                            <comment id="13919159" author="milan.freml" created="Tue, 4 Mar 2014 09:00:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Fixes the error by enveloping function yylex in extern &quot;C&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13924959" author="dimalev" created="Sat, 8 Mar 2014 18:30:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;hi, i have same problem. i fixed it by removing -lfl when linking resulting thrift file. idea comes from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-865&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-865&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
maybe it&apos;s issue about autoconf or automake versions? i have autoconf-2.69 and automake-1.14 installed on my system. i installed required versions are 2.65 &amp;amp;&amp;amp; 1.11, and had troubles with ./configure invocation, and finally the same issue with yylex.&lt;br/&gt;
i am complete newbee in C tools, just sharing my experience.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13940480" author="jfarrell" created="Wed, 19 Mar 2014 14:00:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
